# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files/ for more about ignoring files.

# dependencies
/node_modules
/.pnp
.pnp.*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/versions

# testing
/coverage

# next.js
/.next/
/out/

# production
/build

# misc
.DS_Store
*.pem

# debug
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)
.env*

# vercel
.vercel

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# Internal working files live in /_internal/ (root cleanup refactor, 2026-07-24 — replaces the old
# root-level /_* + "!" exception scheme). _internal/ itself IS tracked: git + the private GitHub repo
# is the project's living backup (repo is private, DRK-internal; none of this is served by the
# deployed site — .vercelignore keeps it off Vercel). Only true scratch inside it stays ignored:
# stale file copies, test images, content-scratch images (masters live in Google Drive + Sanity),
# skill packaging, logs, zips. Note: "_"-prefixed folders inside src/app/ are a real, committed
# Next.js routing convention (e.g. _components/, _lib/) — nothing here touches those.
/_internal/backup/
/_internal/image-test/
/_internal/content-scratch/
/_internal/skill-image-retouch/
/_internal/*.zip
/_internal/*.log
